        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Corinthians 7:6-7",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The sense here is, that their steadfastness was a great source of comfort to him in his trials. It was an instance where the holy lives and the fidelity of a people did much, as will always be the case, to lighten the burdens and cheer the heart of a minister of the gospel. In the inevitable trials of the ministerial office there is no source of comfort more rich and pure than this. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
