        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "over",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (as in last clause), not ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "in",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". It was not simply that Timothy’s tidings brought comfort to the Apostle ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "amidst",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " his present trials; but this comfort ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "bore upon",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " those trials. The steadfastness of the Thessalonians heartened him to meet his troubles at Corinth. This effect of Silas and Timothy’s arrival “from Macedonia” is hinted in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 18:5",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
